# Project core

## Identity

- **Goal**: Integrate RFID/NFC tag streams with SLAM (`slam_toolbox`) and TurtleBot3; robot vs server split via Docker where applicable.
- **Canonical ROS workspace**: `ros2_ws/src/`. Do not reintroduce duplicate packages at repo root.

## Scope discipline

- Change only what the task requires; avoid drive-by refactors in `turtlebot3/` or unrelated packages.
- Do not commit `build/`, `install/`, `log/` (see `.gitignore`).

## Citation

- When referencing existing code in replies, use Cursor code citation format with path and line range.

## Testing / quality

- Python under `ros2_ws/src`: `ament_flake8` / `colcon test` expectations; Ruff config in `pyproject.toml` (no `I*` rules — conflicts with ament import order).
- Prefer `./scripts/lint.sh` before large Python edits; use `./scripts/build_ros.sh` when validating native builds (requires sourced ROS).
